<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-24T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 24,
                                        1928—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>237. Your telegram No. 558, July 22, 10 a.m. According to the
                            Department’s information, the Navy Department will proceed, in
                            accordance with General Butler’s plan as modified by Admiral Bristol,
                            with the reduction of forces.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>